Wanted to give this place 5 stars, but couldn't because they have no beers on tap, and a very limited selection of bottled beers.  However, this is a great little neighborhood pizza joint.  The staff was friendly and attentive, and the open kitchen with it's large brick oven adds a nice touch to the dining room.   I had the Pepperoni and Ham Rollatini, and it was delicious. The meat inside was perfectly balanced with the cheese, and the crust had a crispness that you can only get from a brick oven.  Everything at Crust was great and I'm sure I'll be back soon.

